{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858854030,"sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","part":{"id":"prt_d796fa6a4001eSJNJ8zgeieXmL","messageID":"msg_d796f97be001YE76GNloam78r6","sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_6b1fcdaf77d1403b86a8c463","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"**/cmd/**/*.go"},"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cmd/agentd/main.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cmd/picod/main.go","metadata":{"count":2,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z","time":{"start":1775858854017,"end":1775858854028}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858854036,"sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","part":{"id":"prt_d796fa19f0015HDH6nEhQWH17Z","messageID":"msg_d796f97be001YE76GNloam78r6","sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_30ffb49b5e564cae9d7781f9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Agentd idle cleanup controller in `pkg/agentd`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-018\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/agentd`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: S\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The Agentd idle cleanup controller monitors AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in the cluster. It periodically checks for idle resources (based on last activity timestamp) and deletes them to free up cluster resources. This controller integrates with the existing client-go library (`pkg/client`) for CRUD operations on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-018-001: Controller initialization with Kubernetes client\n25: \n26: The Agentd idle cleanup controller SHALL initialize with a Kubernetes client and shared informers.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-018-001-A — Controller initializes with valid kubeconfig\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file is present at `~/.kube/config`\n31: - **WHEN** the Agentd idle cleanup controller starts\n32: - **THEN** the controller creates a Kubernetes clientset using `clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags`\n33: - **AND** the controller creates a `SharedInformerFactory` for `runtime/v1alpha1` API group\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: AR-018-001-B — Controller initializes informers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n36: \n37: - **GIVEN** the controller has created a `SharedInformerFactory`\n38: - **WHEN** `informerFactory.Start(stopCh)` is called\n39: - **THEN** informers for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` begin caching resources\n40: - **AND** `informerFactory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)` returns true for both informers\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ### AR-018-002: Idle timeout configuration\n45: \n46: The controller SHALL use configurable idle timeout values from environment variables or defaults.\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: AR-018-002-A — Controller uses default idle timeout when env not set\n49: \n50: - **GIVEN** environment variable `AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT` is not set\n51: - **WHEN** the controller creates its configuration\n52: - **THEN** the idle timeout defaults to 15 minutes\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-018-002-B — Controller uses custom idle timeout from environment\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** environment variable `AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT=30m`\n57: - **WHEN** the controller creates its configuration\n58: - **THEN** the idle timeout is set to 30 minutes\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: AR-018-002-C — Controller uses custom check interval from environment\n61: \n62: - **GIVEN** environment variable `AGENTD_CHECK_INTERVAL=5m`\n63: - **WHEN** the controller creates its configuration\n64: - **THEN** the controller runs its idle check every 5 minutes\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ### AR-018-003: Idle detection for AgentRuntime\n69: \n70: The controller SHALL detect idle AgentRuntime resources based on last activity time.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: AR-018-003-A — AgentRuntime is idle when no recent activity\n73: \n74: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime resource exists with `lastActivityAt` timestamp older than idle timeout\n75: - **WHEN** the idle checker evaluates this AgentRuntime\n76: - **THEN** the resource is marked as idle\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: AR-018-003-B — AgentRuntime is not idle when recently active\n79: \n80: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime resource exists with `lastActivityAt` timestamp within idle timeout window\n81: - **WHEN** the idle checker evaluates this AgentRuntime\n82: - **THEN** the resource is NOT marked as idle\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: AR-018-003-C — AgentRuntime without activity timestamp uses creation time\n85: \n86: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime resource exists without `lastActivityAt` annotation\n87: - **WHEN** the idle checker evaluates this AgentRuntime\n88: - **THEN** the resource uses `metadata.creationTimestamp` for idle calculation\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ### AR-018-004: Idle detection for CodeInterpreter\n93: \n94: The controller SHALL detect idle CodeInterpreter resources based on last activity time.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: AR-018-004-A — CodeInterpreter is idle when no recent activity\n97: \n98: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter resource exists with `lastActivityAt` timestamp older than idle timeout\n99: - **WHEN** the idle checker evaluates this CodeInterpreter\n100: - **THEN** the resource is marked as idle\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: AR-018-004-B — CodeInterpreter is not idle when recently active\n103: \n104: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter resource exists with `lastActivityAt` timestamp within idle timeout window\n105: - **WHEN** the idle checker evaluates this CodeInterpreter\n106: - **THEN** the resource is NOT marked as idle\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ### AR-018-005: Idle resource cleanup\n111: \n112: The controller SHALL delete idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: AR-018-005-A — Controller deletes idle AgentRuntime\n115: \n116: - **GIVEN** an idle AgentRuntime resource named \"test-ar\" exists in namespace \"default\"\n117: - **WHEN** the cleanup controller processes the idle resource\n118: - **THEN** `agentRuntimeClient.AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Delete(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})` is called\n119: - **AND** the resource is removed from the cluster\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: AR-018-005-B — Controller deletes idle CodeInterpreter\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** an idle CodeInterpreter resource named \"test-ci\" exists in namespace \"default\"\n124: - **WHEN** the cleanup controller processes the idle resource\n125: - **THEN** `codeInterpreterClient.CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Delete(ctx, \"test-ci\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})` is called\n126: - **AND** the resource is removed from the cluster\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: AR-018-005-C — Cleanup continues when delete fails for one resource\n129: \n130: - **GIVEN** two idle AgentRuntime resources exist: \"ar-1\" and \"ar-2\"\n131: - **AND** deleting \"ar-1\" returns an error\n132: - **WHEN** the cleanup controller processes both resources\n133: - **THEN** the controller attempts to delete \"ar-2\" despite the previous failure\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ### AR-018-006: Periodic cleanup loop\n138: \n139: The controller SHALL run periodic cleanup cycles at configured intervals.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: AR-018-006-A — Cleanup runs at configured interval\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** `AGENTD_CHECK_INTERVAL=5m` is set\n144: - **WHEN** the controller starts its cleanup loop\n145: - **THEN** the cleanup cycle executes every 5 minutes\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: AR-018-006-B — Cleanup stops when stop channel is closed\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** the controller is running its periodic cleanup loop\n150: - **WHEN** the stop channel is closed\n151: - **THEN** the cleanup loop terminates gracefully\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: AR-018-006-C — Cleanup processes all namespaces by default\n154: \n155: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime resources exist in \"default\" and \"kube-system\" namespaces\n156: - **WHEN** the cleanup cycle runs\n157: - **THEN** the controller checks idle resources in both namespaces\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ### AR-018-007: Graceful shutdown\n162: \n163: The controller SHALL handle graceful shutdown with configurable grace period.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: AR-018-007-A — Controller uses grace period before deletion\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** an idle AgentRuntime resource exists\n168: - **AND** `AGENTD_GRACE_PERIOD=60s` is configured\n169: - **WHEN** the controller marks the resource for deletion\n170: - **THEN** the deletion uses `metav1.DeleteOptions{GracePeriodSeconds: &gracePeriod}`\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: AR-018-007-B — Controller logs cleanup actions\n173: \n174: - **GIVEN** an idle AgentRuntime resource \"test-ar\" is deleted\n175: - **WHEN** the deletion completes\n176: - **THEN** a log message is emitted: \"Cleaned up idle AgentRuntime\", \"name\": \"test-ar\"\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## Architecture Notes\n181: \n182: ### Data Structures\n183: \n184: ```go\n185: type IdleCleanupConfig struct {\n186: \tIdleTimeout   time.Duration\n187: \tCheckInterval time.Duration\n188: \tGracePeriod   time.Duration\n189: }\n190: \n191: type IdleCleanupController struct {\n192: \tk8sClient       kubernetes.Interface\n193: \tclientset       versioned.Interface\n194: \tarInformer      cache.SharedIndexInformer\n195: \tciInformer      cache.SharedIndexInformer\n196: \tarLister        listersv1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n197: \tciLister        listersv1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n198: \tconfig          *IdleCleanupConfig\n199: }\n200: \n201: func NewIdleCleanupController(\n202: \tk8sClient kubernetes.Interface,\n203: \tclientset versioned.Interface,\n204: \tarInformer cache.SharedIndexInformer,\n205: \tciInformer cache.SharedIndexInformer,\n206: \tconfig *IdleCleanupConfig,\n207: ) *IdleCleanupController\n208: ```\n209: \n210: ### Constants\n211: \n212: | Constant | Value | Description |\n213: |----------|-------|-------------|\n214: | DefaultIdleTimeout | 15m | Default idle timeout duration |\n215: | DefaultCheckInterval | 5m | Default cleanup check interval |\n216: | DefaultGracePeriod | 30s | Default grace period before deletion |\n217: | LastActivityAnnotationKey | agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity | Annotation key for last activity timestamp |\n218: \n219: ### Environment Variables\n220: \n221: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n222: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n223: | AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT | No | 15m | Idle timeout (e.g., \"10m\", \"1h\") |\n224: | AGENTD_CHECK_INTERVAL | No | 5m | Cleanup check interval |\n225: | AGENTD_GRACE_PERIOD | No | 30s | Grace period before deletion |\n226: | AGENTD_NAMESPACE | No | \"\" (all) | Namespace to monitor (empty = all) |\n227: \n228: ### Key Behaviors\n229: \n230: 1. Initialize Kubernetes clientset and shared informers on startup\n231: 2. Use lister to fetch AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources (read-only, efficient)\n232: 3. Check `lastActivityAt` annotation or creation timestamp for idle detection\n233: 4. Delete idle resources using typed clients\n234: 5. Run cleanup loop at configured interval\n235: 6. Log all cleanup actions for audit trail\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ## References\n240: \n241: - Module: `pkg/agentd` (to be created)\n242: - Base: `pkg/client` - generated Kubernetes client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n243: - Related: `pkg/workloadmanager` - handles sandbox expiration logic in `expiration.go`\n244: - Related: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` - defines AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n\n(End of file - total 244 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Agentd idle cleanup controller in `pkg/agentd`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-018\n- **Module**: `pkg/agentd`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe Agentd idle cleanup controller monitors AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in the cluster. It periodically checks for idle resources (based on last activity timestamp) and deletes them to free up cluster resources. This controller integrates with the existing client-go library (`pkg/client`) for CRUD operations on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775858854012,"end":1775858854034}}}}
