{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775858899019,"sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","part":{"id":"prt_d79705849001N58mUJAqAkPtsS","messageID":"msg_d79704bb7001JjZX2X210vgJju","sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858904284,"sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","part":{"id":"prt_d79706971001sqK6D62lI5YHJr","messageID":"msg_d79704bb7001JjZX2X210vgJju","sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1e2d3ecc599849e0b452b350","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement 4 CLI binary entry points in the `cmd` module for the agentcube project: `agentd`, `picod`, `router`, and `workloadmanager`. Each binary serves as a distinct service entry point with its own package structure, configuration, and lifecycle management.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The agentcube project comprises multiple independent services that need to be deployed and run as separate processes in a Kubernetes cluster. Currently, only `agentd` and `picod` have binary entry points. The `router` and `workloadmanager` packages exist but lack standalone binary entry points.\n12: \n13: ### Goal\n14: \n15: Create consistent CLI binary entry points for all 4 core services:\n16: - **agentd** — Kubernetes controller for idle Sandbox cleanup\n17: - **picod** — PicoD execution server\n18: - **router** — HTTP routing, proxy, and session management service\n19: - **workloadmanager** — Workload orchestration and lifecycle management\n20: \n21: ### Value\n22: \n23: - Consistent CLI interface across all services\n24: - Standardized flag parsing and configuration\n25: - Proper signal handling and graceful shutdown\n26: - Independent deployment and scaling of each service\n27: - Clear separation of concerns\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Scope\n32: \n33: ### In-Scope\n34: \n35: | Binary | Package | Description |\n36: |--------|---------|-------------|\n37: | `agentd` | `cmd/agentd` | Kubernetes controller for idle Sandbox cleanup (existing) |\n38: | `picod` | `cmd/picod` | PicoD execution server (existing) |\n39: | `router` | `cmd/router` | HTTP router, proxy, and session management |\n40: | `workloadmanager` | `cmd/workloadmanager` | Workload orchestration service |\n41: \n42: ### Code Structure\n43: \n44: ```\n45: cmd/\n46: ├── agentd/\n47: │   └── main.go                  # Binary entry point (existing)\n48: ├── picod/\n49: │   └── main.go                  # Binary entry point (existing)\n50: ├── router/\n51: │   └── main.go                  # New binary entry point\n52: └── workloadmanager/\n53:     └── main.go                  # New binary entry point\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ### Out-of-Scope\n57: \n58: - Multi-binary combined binary (single binary with subcommands)\n59: - Dynamic service discovery\n60: - Cross-service communication configuration\n61: - Deployment manifests (Helm charts, YAML)\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## Impact Analysis\n66: \n67: ### Dependencies\n68: \n69: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n70: |------------|--------|---------|\n71: | sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime | v0.19.x | Controller framework for agentd |\n72: | k8s.io/client-go | existing | Kubernetes client integration |\n73: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client | internal | Generated client for runtime API |\n74: | k8s.io/apimachinery | existing | Kubernetes types and utilities |\n75: | github.com/gin-gonic/gin | existing | HTTP framework for workloadmanager |\n76: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | existing | Logging |\n77: \n78: ### Upstream\n79: \n80: - **AR-012 Workload Manager** — Provides workload orchestration logic\n81: - **AR-018 Agentd** — Provides idle cleanup controller logic\n82: - **client-go library** — Generated Kubernetes client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n83: \n84: ### Downstream Consumers\n85: \n86: 1. **Kubernetes Cluster** — All 4 services run as Deployments\n87: 2. **Operators** — Manage individual service deployments\n88: 3. **End Users** — Access services via router or directly\n89: \n90: ### Risks\n91: \n92: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n93: |------|----------|------------|\n94: | Inconsistent flag parsing across binaries | Low | Use consistent flag definitions in each main.go |\n95: | Missing graceful shutdown in new binaries | Medium | Implement signal handling in router and workloadmanager |\n96: | Client-go version mismatch | Low | Use consistent version across all binaries |\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## Alternatives Considered\n101: \n102: ### Option 1: Single Binary with Subcommands (Baseline)\n103: \n104: **Approach**: Create one combined binary with subcommands (`agentcube agentd`, `agentcube router`, etc.).\n105: \n106: **Pros**:\n107: - Single binary to deploy\n108: - Shared configuration\n109: - Consistent CLI interface\n110: \n111: **Cons**:\n112: - Larger binary size\n113: - All services must be deployed together\n114: - Cannot scale services independently\n115: \n116: **Decision**: Not selected — requires independent service deployment and scaling.\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ### Option 2: Separate Binaries (Selected)\n121: \n122: **Approach**: Each service has its own binary entry point in `cmd/` directory.\n123: \n124: **Pros**:\n125: - Independent deployment and scaling\n126: - Smaller individual binaries\n127: - Clear separation of concerns\n128: - Matches existing project structure\n129: \n130: **Cons**:\n131: - Multiple binaries to manage\n132: - Some code duplication in flag parsing\n133: \n134: **Decision**: Selected — aligns with existing architecture and deployment requirements.\n135: \n136: ---\n137: \n138: ### Option 3: Shared Framework Binary\n139: \n140: **Approach**: Create a shared CLI framework that all services use.\n141: \n142: **Pros**:\n143: - Consistent behavior across services\n144: - Reduced code duplication\n145: - Centralized configuration\n146: \n147: **Cons**:\n148: - Added complexity\n149: - Tight coupling between services\n150: - Over-engineered for 4 binaries\n151: \n152: **Decision**: Not selected — introduces unnecessary abstraction layer.\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## Implementation Plan\n157: \n158: ### Phase 1: Router Binary\n159: - [ ] Create `cmd/router/main.go`\n160: - [ ] Initialize router config from flags\n161: - [ ] Set up HTTP server with middleware stack\n162: - [ ] Implement graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n163: \n164: ### Phase 2: Workload Manager Binary\n165: - [ ] Create `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n166: - [ ] Initialize workloadmanager config from flags\n167: - [ ] Set up Kubernetes client using pkg/client\n168: - [ ] Implement graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n169: \n170: ### Phase 3: Verification\n171: - [ ] Build all 4 binaries successfully\n172: - [ ] Verify each binary responds to `-h` flag\n173: - [ ] Verify graceful shutdown works for each\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ## Acceptance Criteria\n178: \n179: - [ ] `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` succeeds\n180: - [ ] `go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod` succeeds\n181: - [ ] `go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router` succeeds\n182: - [ ] `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager` succeeds\n183: - [ ] All binaries accept `-h` flag and display usage\n184: - [ ] All binaries handle SIGTERM/SIGINT for graceful shutdown\n185: - [ ] Each binary has consistent flag parsing pattern\n\n(End of file - total 185 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement 4 CLI binary entry points in the `cmd` module for the agentcube project: `agentd`, `picod`, `router`, and `workloadmanager`. Each binary serves as a distinct service entry point with its own package structure, configuration, and lifecycle management.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe agentcube project comprises multiple independent services that need to be deployed and run as separate processes in a Kubernetes cluster. Currently, only `agentd` and `picod` have binary entry points. The `router` and `workloadmanager` packages exist but lack standalone binary entry points.\n\n### Goal\n\nCreate consistent CLI binary entry points for all 4 core services:\n- **agentd** — Kubernetes controller for idle Sandbox cleanup\n- **picod** — PicoD execution server\n- **router** — HTTP routing, proxy, and session management service\n- **workloadmanager** — Workload orchestration and lifecycle management\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775858904274,"end":1775858904280}}}}
