{"type":"text","timestamp":1775858938107,"sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","part":{"id":"prt_d7970ef2a001pdu4ouR6m0NArf","messageID":"msg_d7970da3e001OuWaKGnsDSDKiU","sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context. Let me write the delta-spec.md with proper GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios:","time":{"start":1775858938106,"end":1775858938106}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858975404,"sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","part":{"id":"prt_d7970f0fc001i6dFYDCtsIHGpw","messageID":"msg_d7970da3e001OuWaKGnsDSDKiU","sessionID":"ses_286908c7bffegIYbqmZvCSrsLL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_2727da60446a4bd09c56d0fc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry (4 Binaries)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing CLI binary entry points in `cmd`. Four binaries must be created: `agentd`, `picod`, `router`, and `workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-019\n- **Module**: `cmd`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Dependencies**: client-go library (`pkg/client`) for Kubernetes client integration\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe agentcube project comprises multiple independent services that need to be deployed and run as separate processes in a Kubernetes cluster. Currently, only `agentd` and `picod` have binary entry points. The `router` and `workloadmanager` packages exist in `pkg/` but lack standalone binary entry points in `cmd/`.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-019-001: Router Binary Entry Point\n\nThe router binary SHALL provide an HTTP routing service entry point with configurable flags.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-001-A — Router binary builds successfully\n\n- **GIVEN** the `cmd/router` directory contains a `main.go` file\n- **WHEN** `go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router` is executed\n- **THEN** the build completes without errors\n- **AND** a `router` binary is created in the `bin/` directory\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-001-B — Router binary displays help\n\n- **GIVEN** the router binary has been built successfully\n- **WHEN** `./bin/router -h` is executed\n- **THEN** help text is displayed including available flags:\n  - `--listen` (default: \":8080\")\n  - `--backend-timeout`\n  - `--health-check-interval`\n  - `--rate-limit`\n  - `--auth-enabled`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-001-C — Router binary starts with default configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** the router binary is built and no flags are provided\n- **WHEN** `./bin/router` is executed\n- **THEN** the router starts listening on \":8080\"\n- **AND** responds to `/healthz` endpoint with HTTP 200\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-001-D — Router binary handles SIGTERM gracefully\n\n- **GIVEN** the router binary is running\n- **WHEN** SIGTERM is sent to the process\n- **THEN** the server stops accepting new connections\n- **AND** existing connections are allowed to complete\n- **AND** the process exits with code 0\n\n---\n\n### AR-019-002: Workload Manager Binary Entry Point\n\nThe workload manager binary SHALL provide a workload orchestration service entry point with Kubernetes client integration.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-002-A — Workload manager binary builds successfully\n\n- **GIVEN** the `cmd/workloadmanager` directory contains a `main.go` file\n- **WHEN** `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager` is executed\n- **THEN** the build completes without errors\n- **AND** a `workloadmanager` binary is created in the `bin/` directory\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-002-B — Workload manager binary displays help\n\n- **GIVEN** the workload manager binary has been built successfully\n- **WHEN** `./bin/workloadmanager -h` is executed\n- **THEN** help text is displayed including available flags:\n  - `--port` (default: 8080)\n  - `--kubeconfig` (optional)\n  - `--shutdown-timeout`\n  - `--enable-metrics`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-002-C — Workload manager binary starts with default configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** the workload manager binary is built and no flags are provided\n- **WHEN** `./bin/workloadmanager` is executed\n- **THEN** the server starts listening on port 8080\n- **AND** responds to `/healthz` endpoint with HTTP 200\n- **AND** responds to `/readyz` endpoint with HTTP 200\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-002-D — Workload manager binary handles SIGINT gracefully\n\n- **GIVEN** the workload manager binary is running\n- **WHEN** SIGINT (Ctrl+C) is sent to the process\n- **THEN** the server stops accepting new requests\n- **AND** the HTTP server shuts down within the configured timeout\n- **AND** the process exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-002-E — Workload manager initializes Kubernetes client\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig exists at `~/.kube/config`\n- **WHEN** the workload manager starts\n- **THEN** a Kubernetes clientset is created using `clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags`\n- **AND** informers are initialized for `runtime/v1alpha1` API group\n\n---\n\n### AR-019-003: Agentd Binary Entry Point\n\nThe agentd binary SHALL provide a Kubernetes controller for idle cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-003-A — Agentd binary builds successfully\n\n- **GIVEN** the `cmd/agentd` directory contains a `main.go` file\n- **WHEN** `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` is executed\n- **THEN** the build completes without errors\n- **AND** an `agentd` binary is created in the `bin/` directory\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-003-B — Agentd binary displays help\n\n- **GIVEN** the agentd binary has been built successfully\n- **WHEN** `./bin/agentd -h` is executed\n- **THEN** help text is displayed showing available flags\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-003-C — Agentd binary handles signals gracefully\n\n- **GIVEN** the agentd binary is running\n- **WHEN** SIGTERM is sent to the process\n- **THEN** the controller manager stops\n- **AND** the process exits gracefully\n\n---\n\n### AR-019-004: Picod Binary Entry Point\n\nThe picod binary SHALL provide a PicoD execution server entry point.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-004-A — Picod binary builds successfully\n\n- **GIVEN** the `cmd/picod` directory contains a `main.go` file\n- **WHEN** `go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod` is executed\n- **THEN** the build completes without errors\n- **AND** a `picod` binary is created in the `bin/` directory\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-004-B — Picod binary displays help\n\n- **GIVEN** the picod binary has been built successfully\n- **WHEN** `./bin/picod -h` is executed\n- **THEN** help text is displayed including available flags:\n  - `--port` (default: 8080)\n  - `--workspace`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-004-C — Picod binary handles signals gracefully\n\n- **GIVEN** the picod binary is running\n- **WHEN** SIGINT is sent to the process\n- **THEN** the server stops\n- **AND** the process exits gracefully\n\n---\n\n### AR-019-005: Consistent Flag Parsing Pattern\n\nAll binaries SHALL follow a consistent flag parsing pattern.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-005-A — All binaries use consistent flag initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** any of the four binaries\n- **WHEN** the binary starts\n- **THEN** `klog.InitFlags(nil)` is called\n- **AND** flags are parsed using `flag.Parse()`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-019-005-B — All binaries support --kubeconfig flag\n\n- **GIVEN** the router or workloadmanager binary\n- **WHEN** `--help` is displayed\n- **THEN** a `--kubeconfig` flag is listed for Kubernetes configuration\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\ncmd/\n├── agentd/\n│   └── main.go           # Binary entry point (existing)\n├── picod/\n│   └── main.go           # Binary entry point (existing)\n├── router/\n│   └── main.go           # New binary entry point\n└── workloadmanager/\n    └── main.go           # New binary entry point\n```\n\n### Key Functions\n\n| Binary | Package | Key Function | Description |\n|--------|---------|--------------|-------------|\n| `agentd` | `cmd/agentd` | `main()` | Uses controller-runtime manager |\n| `picod` | `cmd/picod` | `main()` | Creates `picod.Server` |\n| `router` | `pkg/router` | `RunWithSignal(*Config)` | HTTP router with middleware |\n| `workloadmanager` | `pkg/workloadmanager` | `NewServer(*Config, WorkloadManager)` | Workload orchestration API |\n\n### Configuration\n\n| Binary | Config Type | Default Port |\n|--------|-------------|--------------|\n| `agentd` | Manager options | 0 (healthz only) |\n| `picod` | `picod.Config` | 8080 |\n| `router` | `router.Config` | 8080 |\n| `workloadmanager` | `workloadmanager.Config` | 8080 |\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Used By | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| KUBECONFIG | router, workloadmanager | Path to kubeconfig file |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Module: `cmd`\n- Base: `pkg/client` - Generated Kubernetes client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- Related: `pkg/router` - Router implementation\n- Related: `pkg/workloadmanager` - Workload manager implementation\n- Related: AR-018 - Agentd idle cleanup controller\n- Related: AR-012 - Workload Manager service","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cmd/picod/main.go\">\nERROR [24:39] not enough arguments in call to picod.NewServer\n\thave (*picod.Config)\n\twant (*picod.Config, *picod.AuthConfig)\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/expiration_test.go\">\nERROR [94:16] undefined: metav1\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go\">\nERROR [15:2] \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch\" imported and not used\nERROR [66:14] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error value in return statement: *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status does not implement error (missing method Error)\nERROR [81:9] cannot use &metav1.Status{…} (value of type *\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\".Status) as error v